# CODEOWNERS — review gate for sensitive surfaces.
#
# Why: changes to these paths can flip project routing, the approved-users
# list, dispatch logic, or the workflows that run with secrets. A single
# unguarded approval would be enough to compromise the loop end-to-end.
# Requiring @wells review here turns those into deliberate decisions.
#
# Syntax: https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositories-settings-and-customization/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners
# Effect requires branch protection on `main` with "Require review from Code
# Owners" enabled — see docs/security.md.

# Pipeline config (project_to_repo routing, approved user IDs, state names).
/config/pipeline.json           @wells

# Cloudflare Worker source (HMAC verification, dispatch logic, /config endpoint).
/worker/                        @wells

# Reusable workflows + the target-repo stub template.
/.github/workflows/             @wells
/templates/                     @wells

# Setup script that writes secrets into target repos.
/bin/init-target-repo.sh        @wells

# Security runbook itself.
/docs/security.md               @wells

# Self-protect: don't let the guard be silently widened.
/.github/CODEOWNERS             @wells
